Seven & I to Spend $120 Million on Energy-Saving Measures in 6,000 Stores

-- B y   S h u n i c h i   O z a s a
-- 
2011-04-14T04:45:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/seven-i-to-spend-120-million-on-energy-saving-measures-in-6-000-stores.html
Seven & I Holdings Co., owner of
the 7-Eleven convenience-store brand, will spend 10 billion yen
on energy-saving measures, said Yoh Mitani, managing executive
officer of 7-Eleven  Japan .  The company plans to install LED lights and solar panels to
reduce energy use at about 6,000 stores in Tokyo and surrounding
areas, Mitani told reporters today in Tokyo, where Seven & I is
based.  To contact the reporter on this story:
